{"at": "2026-05-31T03:24:42Z", "commit_ref": "9ec6e08", "intent": "spec", "actor": "agent", "kind": "output", "content": "Authored Spec 0022 as an implementable optical-constructor foundation. The spec commits to a .NET 10 F# domain model, JSON/schema persistence, Avalonia.FuncUI desktop shell, stack/source editing, sequential 1D sweep runner, chart/export surface, FuncUI clone audit gate, and an interface-only optimization boundary. It cites verified repository pointers and includes acceptance criteria, files in scope, test artifacts, and external references.\n"}
{"at": "2026-05-31T03:30:49Z", "commit_ref": "9ec6e08", "intent": "spec", "actor": "user", "kind": "output", "content": "+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.Domain/ProjectJson.fs` (new) — JSON load/save and schema validation.\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.Domain/EngineMapping.fs` (new) — project-to-engine conversion.\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.Domain/SweepRunner.fs` (new) — cancellable sequential 1D sweeps.\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.Domain/Export.fs` (new) — CSV export.\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.Domain/Optimization.fs` (new) — interface-only optimization seam.\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.Domain/Schemas/optical-constructor-project.schema.json` (new) — project schema.\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.Domain/Samples/minimal-project.bmproj.json` (new) — minimal sample project.\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.App/OpticalConstructor.App.fsproj` (new) — desktop app project.\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.App/Program.fs` (new) — app entry point.\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.App/App.fs` (new) — Avalonia application setup.\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.App/MainWindow.fs` (new) — main window.\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.App/Model.fs` (new) — UI state and messages.\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.App/Update.fs` (new) — update function and commands.\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.App/View.fs` (new) — workspace view.\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.App/StackEditor.fs` (new) — layer stack editor.\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.App/SourcePanel.fs` (new) — source and sweep editor.\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.App/ChartPanel.fs` (new) — chart/results panel.\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.App/Audit/AuditFuncUIClone.fsx` (new) — clone audit runner.\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.App/Audit/funcui-clone-audit.md` (new) — committed audit result.\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.Tests/OpticalConstructor.Tests.fsproj` (new) — tests for domain and app seams.\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.Tests/UnitTests.fs` (new) — unit conversion tests.\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.Tests/ProjectJsonTests.fs` (new) — schema and round-trip tests.\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.Tests/EngineMappingTests.fs` (new) — conversion and solver smoke tests.\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.Tests/SweepRunnerTests.fs` (new) — sweep, progress, and cancellation tests.\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.Tests/AuditTests.fs` (new) — FuncUI audit gate tests.\n+\n+## Test artifacts\n+\n+- `dotnet test Berreman/Berreman.slnx`\n+- `dotnet run --project Berreman/OpticalConstructor.App/OpticalConstructor.App.fsproj`\n+- `dotnet fsi Berreman/OpticalConstructor.App/Audit/AuditFuncUIClone.fsx`\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.Domain/Samples/minimal-project.bmproj.json`\n+- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor.Domain/Schemas/optical-constructor-project.schema.json`\n+\n+## References\n+\n+- Avalonia.FuncUI repository and MIT license: https://github.com/fsprojects/Avalonia.FuncUI\n+- ScottPlot: https://scottplot.net/\n+- Plotly.NET: https://plotly.net/\n+- FSharp.SystemTextJson: https://github.com/Tarmil/FSharp.SystemTextJson\n+- System.Text.Json: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.text.json\n+- ALGLIB optimization suite: https://www.alglib.net/optimization/\n+- ALGLIB Levenberg-Marquardt: https://www.alglib.net/optimization/levenbergmarquardt.php\n+- RP Photonics Encyclopedia, article on \"Sellmeier Formula\", Dr. Ruediger Paschotta, https://www.rp-photonics.com/sellmeier_formula.html\n\ntokens used\n169,773\nWrote the spec at [specs/0022/.spec-md](C:/GitHub/Berreman/specs/0022/.spec-md) and appended the required history entry via `history_cli` to [specs/0022/.history](C:/GitHub/Berreman/specs/0022/.history).\n\nI kept edits within the allowed scope. The spec is an implementable optical-constructor foundation covering the F#/.NET 10 domain model, JSON/schema persistence, Avalonia.FuncUI app shell, stack/source editing, sweep/chart/export path, FuncUI clone audit gate, and optimization boundary. I also checked the spec for lowercase normative keywords and non-ASCII content."}
